2. Restrictions

   a. COMPETING USE PROHIBITION: You may NOT use the Licensed Work for a
      Competing Use. A "Competing Use" means making the Licensed Work available
      to third parties as a hosted or managed media player service that competes
      with Fairu's media hosting and player services (fairu.app).

      For clarity, the following uses are NOT considered Competing Uses and
      are explicitly permitted:

      - Using the player to embed and play your own media content on your
        websites or applications
      - Using the player with self-hosted media files
      - Using the player with third-party CDNs or hosting services for your
        own content
      - Customizing and modifying the player for your own use
      - Using the player as part of a larger application that is not primarily
        a media player service
      - Internal use within organizations
      - Educational and research purposes
      - Open source projects that do not compete with fairu.app

